messages.text: Hi Dr. Chen, I had a quick question about my Finasteride prescription. Is it okay to take it with my daily vitamin?
Hi Sarah! Yes, it's perfectly safe to take Finasteride with your daily vitamins. Just make sure to take it at the same time each day for best results. Let me know if you have any other questions!
Great, thank you so much!
Quick update - I've been on Finasteride for 6 months now and I'm starting to see some regrowth! Thank you!
Hi Michael, I've reviewed your questionnaire and approved your Semaglutide prescription. You'll start at the 0.25mg dose. Please let me know if you experience any nausea.
Thank you Dr. Patel! I'll keep you posted on my progress.
Update: Down 35 lbs so far! The nausea was mild the first week but went away.
That's fantastic progress Michael! Keep it up. Let me know when you're ready to discuss increasing your dose.
I think I'm ready to move up to 0.5mg. The weight loss has plateaued a bit.
Hi Robert, I've approved your Tadalafil prescription. Taking 5mg daily should help with consistent results. Let me know how it goes.
Thanks Dr. Williams. Quick question - are there any foods I should avoid?
Good question. Avoid excessive grapefruit juice as it can increase the medication levels. Otherwise, no major restrictions.
My card was declined for this month's refill. I'm updating my payment info now.
Hi Jessica, welcome! I've approved your Semaglutide prescription at the 1.0mg dose based on your previous experience with the medication. How has your journey been so far?
Great! I was on it before through another provider but switched for the better pricing here.
Just wanted to let you know I'm down 40 lbs total now. Feeling amazing!
Hi Ashley, I've reviewed your skin concerns and prescribed Tretinoin 0.025%. Start by applying a pea-sized amount every other night for the first 2 weeks.
Thank you Dr. Thompson! Should I expect any peeling?
Yes, mild peeling is normal initially. Use a gentle moisturizer and sunscreen daily. If irritation is severe, skip a night.
Got my shipment! Starting tonight. Thanks!

subjective.chiefComplaint: Hair thinning at crown and temples
subjective.historyOfPresentIllness: Patient reports gradual hair loss over past 2 years. Family history of male pattern baldness on maternal side. No recent stressors or medication changes.
subjective.reviewOfSystems: Denies scalp itching, pain, or skin changes

objective.physicalExam: Photos reviewed - Norwood Stage II-III pattern baldness. No scarring or inflammation noted.

assessment.clinicalImpression: Classic presentation of androgenetic alopecia in 36yo female. Good candidate for Finasteride therapy.

plan.instructions: Continue for minimum 6 months to assess efficacy. Take at same time daily.
plan.followUp: Follow-up in 3 months to assess progress

subjective.historyOfPresentIllness: 49yo male with BMI 34.2, seeking medical weight loss. Has tried diet and exercise with limited success. No history of bariatric surgery.
subjective.reviewOfSystems: Reports occasional heartburn, denies chest pain, shortness of breath

objective.physicalExam: Labs reviewed - HbA1c 5.8% (prediabetic range), lipid panel mildly elevated

assessment.clinicalImpression: Good candidate for GLP-1 therapy given metabolic comorbidities

medications: Semaglutide 0.25mg weekly x 4 weeks, then titrate
plan.instructions: Inject subcutaneously once weekly. Start with 0.25mg, increase to 0.5mg after 4 weeks if tolerated.
plan.followUp: Follow-up in 1 month for dose adjustment

subjective.historyOfPresentIllness: 56yo male with gradual onset ED over past year. Able to achieve partial erections. No morning erections. Denies relationship stress.
subjective.reviewOfSystems: History of hypertension (controlled), denies chest pain, takes lisinopril 10mg daily

objective.physicalExam: Not applicable for telehealth visit. Labs reviewed - testosterone within normal range.

assessment.clinicalImpression: ED likely secondary to vascular changes from hypertension. No contraindication to PDE5 inhibitor.

plan.instructions: Take once daily at same time. May take up to 2 weeks to see full effect.
plan.followUp: Follow-up in 4-6 weeks to assess response

subjective.historyOfPresentIllness: 33yo female transferring care, previously on Semaglutide 1.0mg through another provider. Reports good tolerance and 25 lb weight loss over 6 months.
subjective.reviewOfSystems: No nausea, constipation well-controlled with fiber

assessment.clinicalImpression: Good response to GLP-1 therapy. Continue current dose.

plan.instructions: Continue current regimen. Maintain balanced diet and regular exercise.

subjective.historyOfPresentIllness: 31yo female with persistent adult acne and concerns about skin texture. Has tried OTC products with limited success.

objective.physicalExam: Photos reviewed - mild inflammatory acne on chin and jawline, some post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation, mild textural irregularities

assessment.clinicalImpression: Good candidate for topical retinoid therapy

plan.instructions: Start every other night for 2 weeks, then nightly. Use sunscreen daily. Expect mild peeling initially.
plan.followUp: Follow-up in 6-8 weeks to assess tolerance and efficacy
